Description of the included files:
lab0.c - a single C source module that compiles cleanly (with gcc, with no errors or warnings). The program copies its standard input to its standard output.
Makefile - to build the program and the tarball.
backtrace.png - showing a segfault and associated stack-trace.
breakpoint.png - showing a breakpoint and variable inspection.
README - this file.

Description of the smoke-test cases in check:
1. Test if the program detect and report invalid arguments.
2. Test if the program detect and report non-existent file.
3. Test if the program is able to read from stdin and write to stdout.
4. Test if the program outputs correct content.
5. Test if the program is able to read from --input=filename and write to --output=filename.
6. Test if the program is able to cause segmentation fault.
7. Test if the program is able to catch segmentation fault.

References:
1. test script provided by web.cs.ucla.edu/classes/spring18/cs111/projects/P0_check.sh
2. GNU websites. 
